eba2b52f-969d-5de1-9f06-9e888ab12706,tg:rubgr:206,e73_Descriptions,,id.desc,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,"[recto] Adoration of Brussel: Follows the rich type as popular in the XIV & early XV C. particularly Limburg (Chantilly) [...] See e.g. Antonio Vivarini, Berlin Museum [Berlin, Gemäldegalerie] (H.[Hugo] Kehrer, Die Heiligen drei Könige in Literatur und Kunst, 2 vols. Leipzig, 1908-1909, Vol. II, 1909, Abb. 266 (p. 224) [...]. There seems to be really some connection with Leonardo [...]; [verso] surrounding the holy group [...] though reminiscent of Jan van Eyck or Goes [...]. Adoration with crowds from left and right: Filippino Lippi, Uffizi; The Virgin enveloped in her cloak similarly to Virgin in London Adoration.[scan]",descriptive note,Nederlands,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
